Sleeping with Sirens is an American post-hardcore band from Orlando, Florida currently residing in Grand Rapids, Michigan. The band was formed in 2009 by members of For All We Know, Broadway, and We Are Defiance. They are currently signed to Rise Records and have released two full-length albums and an acoustic EP, "If You Were a Movie, This Would Be Your Soundtrack", which was released on June 26, 2012.
The group is known primarily for the versatility of vocalist Kellin Quinn's tenor leggiero vocal range. Their first album, "With Ears to See and Eyes to Hear", was released on March 23, 2010. Debuted at number 7 on "Billboard"s Top Heatseekers chart, and at number 36 on Top Independent Albums.
Their second album, "Let's Cheers to This", was released on May 10, 2011. The single from the album, "Do It Now Remember It Later", was released on April 7, 2011.
On October 21, 2012, Sleeping With Sirens released a new single called "Dead Walker Texas Ranger" as a halloween special.
In January 2013 the band will enter the studio to record their follow up to Let's Cheers to This with an estimated release date of mid 2013.
